00:01:41.260 --> 00:01:44.260
That's what can happen to our thinking.

00:01:44.260 --> 00:01:51.260
But it doesn't always have a positive effect on our life or our future.

00:01:51.260 --> 00:01:54.260
Those specifically address to a young man.

00:01:54.260 --> 00:02:00.260
The Bible book of Proverbs gives sound advice for all of us.

00:02:00.260 --> 00:02:03.260
Proverbs chapter 1 verse 4 says,

00:02:03.260 --> 00:02:11.259
To give a young man, for that matter any of us, knowledge and thinking ability.

00:02:11.259 --> 00:02:14.259
What is thinking ability in this verse?

00:02:14.259 --> 00:02:22.259
The Hebrew word translated thinking ability can be used in a bad sense or in a favorable one.

00:02:22.259 --> 00:02:30.259
So our mind and thoughts can be directed to a worthy, upright end or just the opposite.

00:02:30.259 --> 00:02:35.259
If we incline our thinking to aspects of Jehovah's will and purposes,

00:02:35.259 --> 00:02:39.259
we'll safeguard our own thinking ability,

00:02:39.259 --> 00:02:43.259
directing it into the right channels.

00:02:43.259 --> 00:02:47.259
How valuable is that type of thinking process?

00:02:47.259 --> 00:02:51.259
Turn to Proverbs chapter 3 verses 21 and 22,

00:02:51.259 --> 00:02:52.259
which states,

00:02:52.259 --> 00:02:57.259
safeguard practical wisdom and thinking ability.

00:02:57.259 --> 00:03:00.259
They will give you life.

00:03:00.259 --> 00:03:05.259
Thinking ability is not in the exclusive realm of the studious type.

00:03:06.259 --> 00:03:15.259
Throughout our entire life, we take in information by reading, seeing, hearing and experiencing things.

00:03:15.259 --> 00:03:24.259
And it's the way we take in information and react to it that shapes our individual behavior and personality.

00:03:24.259 --> 00:03:31.259
Many persons have not used their minds for much more than the essentials of daily living.

00:03:31.259 --> 00:03:35.259
But to succeed in life and in Jehovah's eyes,

00:03:35.259 --> 00:03:42.259
it's necessary that we learn to train, develop and guard thinking ability.

00:03:42.259 --> 00:03:51.259
Consider how trained thinking ability might protect us when it comes to using the Internet wisely.

00:03:51.259 --> 00:03:55.259
While the Internet can be an excellent tool for gathering knowledge,

00:03:55.259 --> 00:04:02.259
thinking ability when properly exercised will safeguard us from its harmful effects.

00:04:02.259 --> 00:04:04.259
For example,

00:04:04.259 --> 00:04:14.259
some popular social media sites contain short videos designed to deliver instant gratification.

00:04:14.259 --> 00:04:18.259
If the viewer gets no immediate emotional reward,

00:04:18.259 --> 00:04:25.259
he is tempted to keep scrolling to find material that will give the desired effect.

00:04:25.259 --> 00:04:29.259
Now over time, this can lure one's attention span,

00:04:29.259 --> 00:04:37.259
which may impede a person's ability to learn, retain and recall information.

00:04:37.259 --> 00:04:43.259
None of us would want that to happen to us, would we?

00:04:43.259 --> 00:04:49.259
Additionally, studies have shown that those who spend too much of their time with their electronic devices

00:04:49.259 --> 00:04:57.259
are more prone to stress, anxiety, depression or other mental health problems.

00:04:57.259 --> 00:05:06.259
On the other hand, thinking ability can help us to work out ways to control our use of such technology.

00:05:06.259 --> 00:05:18.259
For example, God oriented thinking ability can help us to distinguish truth from misleading and false information.

00:05:18.259 --> 00:05:25.259
Thus there is wisdom in what is stated in Proverbs chapter 2 verses 11 and 12.

00:05:25.259 --> 00:05:30.259
Thinking ability will keep watch over you,

00:05:30.259 --> 00:05:37.259
and discernment will safeguard you to save you from the bad course.

00:05:37.259 --> 00:05:41.259
Why is this so important?

00:05:41.259 --> 00:05:47.259
Well, thinking ability and discernment gives us perception,

00:05:47.259 --> 00:05:52.259
and perception is closely related to our conscience.

00:05:53.259 --> 00:05:59.259
What we have meditated on from God's Word and stored in our mind can mold our conscience,

00:05:59.259 --> 00:06:06.259
which is an inner mechanism to warn us of wrong actions or tendencies.

00:06:06.259 --> 00:06:11.259
In effect, our thinking watches over us.

00:06:11.259 --> 00:06:17.259
Now notice how this is alluded to at Hebrews chapter 5 and verse 14.

00:06:17.259 --> 00:06:24.259
But solid food belongs to mature people, to those who through use have their powers of discernment

00:06:24.259 --> 00:06:30.259
